{"type":"message","id":"06a1d2a4","parentId":"5985fd0a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:52:20.375Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script ran but there was an error - the LLM response was empty or null. Let me read the pulse log file to see what happened.","thinkingSignature":"531ff058f8bf4588ea9022713aea2338ad01d05f403858461a5b327c4fed3d3a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wy82y48fhp32_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 045115.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":594,"output":85,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12633,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774342337645}}
{"type":"message","id":"20e02628","parentId":"06a1d2a4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:52:20.384Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wy82y48fhp32_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 045115\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n2. Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n3. Pending: TIC Experiment - Implement Temporal Invariance Compression classifier on logs/pulse_*.md files\r\n\r\nThe next action is clear: implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on the pulse logs to test the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis.\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the logs directory to understand the format of pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\n\r\nThe TIC experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. The pulse logs exist in `logs/` but no classifier exists yet to test invariant/variant classification and next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\n\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs for temporal invariants, implements the compression-causal duality hypothesis, and outputs classification accuracy metrics against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis:\r\n  Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n  Compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n  - >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n  - >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir: str = \"logs\"):\r\n        self.logs_dir = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        self.pulses: List[Dict] = []\r\n        self.invariants: List[str] = []\r\n        self.variants: List[str] = []\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self) -> int:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse logs sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n        for pf in pulse_files:\r\n            with open(pf, 'r') as f:\r\n                content = f.read()\r\n            self.pulses.append({\r\n                'file': pf.name,\r\n                'content': content,\r\n                'lines': content.split('\\n')\r\n            })\r\n        return len(self.pulses)\r\n    \r\n    def extract_tokens(self, text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract meaningful tokens from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n        # Remove timestamps, file paths, markdown\r\n        text = re.sub(r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}[\\s\\d:]+', ' ', text)\r\n        text = re.sub(r'[a-zA-Z]:\\\\[^\\s]+', ' ', text)\r\n        text = re.sub(r'[a-z_/]+\\.(md|ps1|png|py)', ' ', text)\r\n        text = re.sub(r'[#*`>\\-]', ' ', text)\r\n        # Extract key terms\r\n        tokens = [t.lower() for t in re.findall(r'\\b[a-z]{4,}\\b', text)]\r\n        return tokens\r\n    \r\n    def find_invariants(self) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Find tokens that appear consistently across pulses (invariants).\"\"\"\r\n        all_tokens = [self.extract_tokens(p['content']) for p in self.pulses]\r\n        token_freq = Counter()\r\n        for tokens in all_tokens:\r\n            token_freq.update(set(tokens))  # Unique per pulse\r\n        \r\n        total_pulses = len(self.pulses)\r\n        invariants = {}\r\n        variants = {}\r\n        \r\n        for token, count in token_freq.items():\r\n            ratio = count / total_pulses\r\n            if ratio >= 0.6:  # Appears in 60%+ of pulses = invariant\r\n                invariants[token] = ratio\r\n            elif ratio <= 0.3:  # Appears in <30% of pulses = variant\r\n                variants[token] = ratio\r\n        \r\n        self.invariants = list(invariants.keys())\r\n        self.variants = list(variants.keys())\r\n        return {'invariants': len(invariants), 'variants': len(variants)}\r\n    \r\n    def classify_content(self, content: str) -> Tuple[float, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify content as invariant-rich or variant-rich.\"\"\"\r\n        tokens = self.extract_tokens(content)\r\n        if not tokens:\r\n            return 0.5, 0.5\r\n        \r\n        inv_count = sum(1 for t in tokens if t in self.invariants)\r\n        var_count = sum(1 for t in tokens if t in self.variants)\r\n        total = len(tokens)\r\n        \r\n        inv_ratio = inv_count / total if total > 0 else 0\r\n        var_ratio = var_count / total if total > 0 else 0\r\n        return inv_ratio, var_ratio\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, current_pulse: Dict) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Predict key tokens likely in next pulse based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n        # Next pulse should maintain invariants + introduce variants\r\n        current_tokens = set(self.extract_tokens(current_pulse['content']))\r\n        predicted = []\r\n        \r\n        # Must-haves: invariants\r\n        predicted.extend(self.invariants[:10])\r\n        \r\n        # Possible variants: current content patterns\r\n        predicted.extend([t for t in current_tokens if t not in self.invariants][:5])\r\n        return predicted[:15]\r\n    \r\n    def evaluate(self) -> Dict:\r\n        \"\"\"Run full TIC experiment evaluation.\"\"\"\r\n        if not self.pulses:\r\n            self.load_pulses()\r\n        \r\n        if not self.invariants:\r\n            self.find_invariants()\r\n        \r\n        # Classification accuracy\r\n        correct = 0\r\n        total = 0\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:51:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774342340382}}
